init_text:
Are We Being Bad Citizens If We Don't Keep Up With the News?

In your opinion, are we being bad citizens if we don't keep up with the news? Do you think all people have some responsibility to know what is going on in the world? Does engaging with current events actually do anything at all? Why do you think the way you do?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I say do your own research with reputable sources, read articles from different sites that oppose the one your reading and see if their arguments are backed by facts

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Science education, critical thinking and objective reasoning are slowly being destroyed in schools and by media.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: And this is what is making the world a worse place.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Unfortunately media has been doing this more and more.
